---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PostCard from "../components/PostCard.astro";
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";

const posts = (await getCollection("blog"))
  .sort((a, b) => b.data.date.valueOf() - a.data.date.valueOf())
  .slice(0, 3);
const withBase = (path = "") => `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "")}/${path}`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Dare to Break Free | Stories of Living, Learning & Letting Go">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Southampton, UK</p>
      <h1>Dare to Break Free</h1>
      <p class="lede">This isn't a polished success story. It's the messy middle, the wrong turns, and the contradictions that come with trying to build a better life.</p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href={withBase("blog/")}>Read the blog</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href={withBase("share-your-story/")}>Share Your Story</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section two-column">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">The story</p>
      <h2>The addiction, ambition, survival, self-destruction and reinvention.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="stack">
      <p>I've spent more than twenty years trying to understand what healing really means for me mentally, physically, and spiritually. Some things helped. Others slowly became another form of escape or self-destruction.</p>
      <p>This space is where I write about the things we're usually taught to tidy up before we show them to the world.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section two-column soft-band">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">What lives here</p>
      <h2>None of it is wrapped up neatly.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="stack">
      <p>The pressure to hold it together. The identities we outgrow. Neurodiversity and feeling different long before you have words for it. Addiction in all its forms. Burnout. Midlife.</p>
      <p>Starting over when you thought you'd already figured life out. Wanting more from life while also wanting to disappear from it.</p>
      <p>Some of it comes from my memoir. Some of it comes from where life has taken me since.</p>
      <p>If you've ever felt trapped by who you were supposed to be, you're probably in the right place.</p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href={withBase("blog/")}>Read the blog</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Latest writing</p>
      <h2>From the blog</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="post-grid">
      {posts.map((post) => <PostCard post={post} />)}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Stay close to the story</p>
      <h2>Join the email list</h2>
      <p>Occasional notes, new posts, and book updates. No noise, no performance.</p>
    </div>
    <a class="button" href={withBase("contact/")}>Subscribe</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
